events.description: The Sapienza University of Rome is instituted by a bull of Pope Boniface VIII.
events.html: • 1303 – The Sapienza University of Rome is instituted by a bull of Pope Boniface VIII.[1]

events.description: Oliver Cromwell dissolves England's Rump Parliament.
events.html: • 1653 – Oliver Cromwell dissolves England's Rump Parliament.[2]

events.description: English Admiral Robert Blake destroys a Spanish silver fleet, under heavy fire from the shore, at the Battle of Santa Cruz de Tenerife.
events.html: • 1657 – English Admiral Robert Blake destroys a Spanish silver fleet, under heavy fire from the shore, at the Battle of Santa Cruz de Tenerife.[3]

entities.name: Battle of Santa Cruz de Tenerife (1657)

events.description: Freedom of religion is granted to the Jews of New Amsterdam (later New York City).
events.html: • 1657 – Freedom of religion is granted to the Jews of New Amsterdam (later New York City).

events.description: Start of Konbaung–Hanthawaddy War, a new phase in the Burmese Civil War (1740–57).
events.html: • 1752 – Start of Konbaung–Hanthawaddy War, a new phase in the Burmese Civil War (1740–57).

events.description: The Georgian king, Erekle II, abandoned by his Russian ally Count Totleben, wins a victory over Ottoman forces at Aspindza.
events.html: • 1770 – The Georgian king, Erekle II, abandoned by his Russian ally Count Totleben, wins a victory over Ottoman forces at Aspindza.

events.description: American Revolutionary War: The Siege of Boston begins, following the battles at Lexington and Concord.
events.html: • 1775 – American Revolutionary War: The Siege of Boston begins, following the battles at Lexington and Concord.

events.description: George Washington arrives at Grays Ferry, Philadelphia, while en route to Manhattan for his inauguration.
events.html: • 1789 – George Washington arrives at Grays Ferry, Philadelphia, while en route to Manhattan for his inauguration.

events.description: France declares war against the "King of Hungary and Bohemia", the beginning of the French Revolutionary Wars.
events.html: • 1792 – France declares war against the "King of Hungary and Bohemia", the beginning of the French Revolutionary Wars.

events.description: The Septinsular Republic is established.
events.html: • 1800 – The Septinsular Republic is established.

events.description: Two Austrian army corps in Bavaria are defeated by a First French Empire army led by Napoleon at the Battle of Abensberg on the second day of a four-day campaign that ended in a French victory.
events.html: • 1809 – Two Austrian army corps in Bavaria are defeated by a First French Empire army led by Napoleon at the Battle of Abensberg on the second day of a four-day campaign that ended in a French victory.

events.description: René Caillié becomes the second non-Muslim to enter Timbuktu, following Major Gordon Laing. He would also be the first to return alive.
events.html: • 1828 – René Caillié becomes the second non-Muslim to enter Timbuktu, following Major Gordon Laing. He would also be the first to return alive.[4]

events.description: U.S. Congress passes an act creating the Wisconsin Territory.
events.html: • 1836 – U.S. Congress passes an act creating the Wisconsin Territory.

events.description: American Civil War: Robert E. Lee resigns his commission in the United States Army in order to command the forces of the state of Virginia.
events.html: • 1861 – American Civil War: Robert E. Lee resigns his commission in the United States Army in order to command the forces of the state of Virginia.[5]

events.description: Thaddeus S. C. Lowe, attempting to display the value of balloons, makes record journey, flying 900 miles from Cincinnati to South Carolina.
events.html: • 1861 – Thaddeus S. C. Lowe, attempting to display the value of balloons, makes record journey, flying 900 miles from Cincinnati to South Carolina.[6]

events.description: Louis Pasteur and Claude Bernard complete the experiment disproving the theory of spontaneous generation.
events.html: • 1862 – Louis Pasteur and Claude Bernard complete the experiment disproving the theory of spontaneous generation.

events.description: Astronomer Angelo Secchi demonstrates the Secchi disk, which measures water clarity, aboard Pope Pius IX's yacht, the L'Immaculata Concezion.
events.html: • 1865 – Astronomer Angelo Secchi demonstrates the Secchi disk, which measures water clarity, aboard Pope Pius IX's yacht, the L'Immaculata Concezion.

events.description: The April Uprising begins. Its suppression shocks European opinion, and Bulgarian independence becomes a condition for ending the Russo-Turkish War.
events.html: • 1876 – The April Uprising begins. Its suppression shocks European opinion, and Bulgarian independence becomes a condition for ending the Russo-Turkish War.

events.description: Pope Leo XIII publishes the encyclical Humanum genus, condemning Freemasonry.
events.html: • 1884 – Pope Leo XIII publishes the encyclical Humanum genus, condemning Freemasonry.

events.description: U.S. President William McKinley signs a joint resolution to Congress for declaration of war against Spain, beginning the Spanish–American War.
events.html: • 1898 – U.S. President William McKinley signs a joint resolution to Congress for declaration of war against Spain, beginning the Spanish–American War.[7]

events.description: Pierre and Marie Curie refine radium chloride.
events.html: • 1902 – Pierre and Marie Curie refine radium chloride.

events.description: Opening day of competition in the New South Wales Rugby League.
events.html: • 1908 – Opening day of competition in the New South Wales Rugby League.[8]

events.description: Nineteen men, women, and children participating in a strike are killed in the Ludlow Massacre during the Colorado Coalfield War.
events.html: • 1914 – Nineteen men, women, and children participating in a strike are killed in the Ludlow Massacre during the Colorado Coalfield War.[9]

events.description: Manfred von Richthofen, a.k.a. The Red Baron, shoots down his 79th and 80th victims, his final victories before his death the following day.
events.html: • 1918 – Manfred von Richthofen, a.k.a. The Red Baron, shoots down his 79th and 80th victims, his final victories before his death the following day.

events.description: The Soviet government creates South Ossetian Autonomous Oblast within Georgian SSR.
events.html: • 1922 – The Soviet government creates South Ossetian Autonomous Oblast within Georgian SSR.

events.description: World War II: U.S. troops capture Leipzig, Germany, only to later cede the city to the Soviet Union.
events.html: • 1945 – World War II: U.S. troops capture Leipzig, Germany, only to later cede the city to the Soviet Union.

events.description: World War II: Führerbunker: On his 56th birthday Adolf Hitler makes his last trip to the surface to award Iron Crosses to boy soldiers of the Hitler Youth.
events.html: • 1945 – World War II: Führerbunker: On his 56th birthday Adolf Hitler makes his last trip to the surface to award Iron Crosses to boy soldiers of the Hitler Youth.

events.description: Twenty Jewish children used in medical experiments at Neuengamme are killed in the basement of the Bullenhuser Damm school.
events.html: • 1945 – Twenty Jewish children used in medical experiments at Neuengamme are killed in the basement of the Bullenhuser Damm school.

events.description: Amethyst incident: The People's Liberation Army attacks the HMS Amethyst (F116) travelling to the British embassy in Nanjing during the Chinese Civil War.
events.html: • 1949 – Amethyst incident: The People's Liberation Army attacks the HMS Amethyst (F116) travelling to the British embassy in Nanjing during the Chinese Civil War.[10]

events.description: The League of Nations officially dissolves, giving most of its power to the United Nations.
events.html: • 1946 – The League of Nations officially dissolves, giving most of its power to the United Nations.

events.description: Cold War: Failure of the Bay of Pigs Invasion of US-backed Cuban exiles against Cuba.
events.html: • 1961 – Cold War: Failure of the Bay of Pigs Invasion of US-backed Cuban exiles against Cuba.

events.description: English politician Enoch Powell makes his controversial "Rivers of Blood" speech.
events.html: • 1968 – English politician Enoch Powell makes his controversial "Rivers of Blood" speech.[11]

events.description: South African Airways Flight 228 crashes near the Hosea Kutako International Airport in South West Africa (now Namibia), killing 123 people.
events.html: • 1968 – South African Airways Flight 228 crashes near the Hosea Kutako International Airport in South West Africa (now Namibia), killing 123 people.[12]

events.description: Apollo program: Apollo 16 Lunar Module, commanded by John Young and piloted by Charles Duke, lands on the Moon.
events.html: • 1972 – Apollo program: Apollo 16 Lunar Module, commanded by John Young and piloted by Charles Duke, lands on the Moon.

events.description: Air France Flight 422 crashes after taking off from El Dorado International Airport in Bogotá, Colombia, killing all 53 people on board.
events.html: • 1998 – Air France Flight 422 crashes after taking off from El Dorado International Airport in Bogotá, Colombia, killing all 53 people on board.[13]

events.description: Columbine High School massacre: Eric Harris and Dylan Klebold kill 13 people and injure 24 others before committing suicide at Columbine High School in Columbine, Colorado.
events.html: • 1999 – Columbine High School massacre: Eric Harris and Dylan Klebold kill 13 people and injure 24 others before committing suicide at Columbine High School in Columbine, Colorado.[14]

events.description: Johnson Space Center shooting: William Phillips barricades himself with a handgun in NASA's Johnson Space Center in Houston, Texas before killing a male hostage and himself.
events.html: • 2007 – Johnson Space Center shooting: William Phillips barricades himself with a handgun in NASA's Johnson Space Center in Houston, Texas before killing a male hostage and himself.[16]

events.description: Danica Patrick wins the Indy Japan 300 becoming the first female driver in history to win an Indy car race.
events.html: • 2008 – Danica Patrick wins the Indy Japan 300 becoming the first female driver in history to win an Indy car race.[17]

events.description: The Deepwater Horizon drilling rig explodes in the Gulf of Mexico, killing eleven workers and beginning an oil spill that would last six months.
events.html: • 2010 – The Deepwater Horizon drilling rig explodes in the Gulf of Mexico, killing eleven workers and beginning an oil spill that would last six months.

events.description: One hundred twenty-seven people are killed when a plane crashes in a residential area near the Benazir Bhutto International Airport near Islamabad, Pakistan.
events.html: • 2012 – One hundred twenty-seven people are killed when a plane crashes in a residential area near the Benazir Bhutto International Airport near Islamabad, Pakistan.

events.description: A 6.6-magnitude earthquake strikes Lushan County, Ya'an, in China's Sichuan province, killing at least 193 people and injuring thousands.
events.html: • 2013 – A 6.6-magnitude earthquake strikes Lushan County, Ya'an, in China's Sichuan province, killing at least 193 people and injuring thousands.

events.description: Ten people are killed in a bomb attack on a convoy carrying food supplies to a United Nations compound in Garowe in the Somali region of Puntland.
events.html: • 2015 – Ten people are killed in a bomb attack on a convoy carrying food supplies to a United Nations compound in Garowe in the Somali region of Puntland.

events.description: For the first time in history, oil prices drop below zero, an effect of the 2020 Russia-Saudi Arabia oil price war.
events.html: • 2020 – For the first time in history, oil prices drop below zero, an effect of the 2020 Russia-Saudi Arabia oil price war.[18]

events.description: State of Minnesota v. Derek Michael Chauvin: Derek Chauvin is found guilty of all charges in the murder of George Floyd by the Fourth Judicial District Court of Minnesota.
events.html: • 2021 – State of Minnesota v. Derek Michael Chauvin: Derek Chauvin is found guilty of all charges in the murder of George Floyd by the Fourth Judicial District Court of Minnesota.[19]

entities.name: State of Minnesota v. Derek Michael Chauvin

events.description: SpaceX's Starship rocket, the largest and most powerful rocket ever built, launches for the first time. It explodes 4 minutes into flight.
events.html: • 2023 – SpaceX's Starship rocket, the largest and most powerful rocket ever built, launches for the first time. It explodes 4 minutes into flight.[20]
